This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on real-world problems such as robotics and the deployment of reinforcement learning algorithms on real robots. It also mentions sim-to-real approaches, which are commonly used in robotics research. 

The paper also discusses the use of Q-learning, which is a popular reinforcement learning algorithm, suggesting that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The connection between information theoretic MPC and entropy regularized RL suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. 

The use of biased models and the challenges of learning an accurate global value function or policy suggest that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

Finally, the use of Q-learning and the focus on optimization suggest that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
